The paper deals with optimization problems in relay networks, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The focus is on computing the cut-set bound, which is a fundamental concept in network coding and information theory. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem and proposes a technique to reduce it, which falls under the category of algorithms and complexity (cs.DS). The simulations and comparisons with other scheduling approaches involve performance evaluation and statistical analysis (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents results on polynomial time algorithms for certain network topologies, which is related to the area of machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
